The paper deals with pitch detection in speech processing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and audio processing. The use of traditional machine learning methods and acoustic features from multiple domains suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). However, the use of deep learning techniques in recent papers suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the assessment of discrimination power through mutual information suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
